25 who there where earth and heaven obeyed,
26 a woman, alone and just then created,
27 did not endure to remain under any veil;

34 before us, like a burning fire,
35 the air beneath the green boughs became for us;
36 and the sweet sound was already perceived as singing.

43 A little farther on, seven trees of gold
44 falsified in appearance the long stretch
45 of the space that was still between us and them;

64 Then I saw people, as if following their leaders,
65 coming behind, dressed in white;
66 and such whiteness was never seen here on earth.

73 and I saw the little flames going ahead,
74 leaving the air painted behind them,
